WEBVTT

00:00:00.240 --> 00:00:03.030
Hey, Happy Thanksgiving, everybody. Thank

00:00:03.040 --> 00:00:05.910
you for joining us. Well, praise the Lord.

00:00:05.920 --> 00:00:07.590
I want to give God thanks for all the

00:00:07.600 --> 00:00:10.190
things that He's done for us. I mean, man,

00:00:10.200 --> 00:00:12.830
God's been good this year. You know,

00:00:12.840 --> 00:00:15.990
if you go back and reflect on all

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:18.109
the things the Lord has done, what has He

00:00:18.119 --> 00:00:20.950
done for you? I want you to—it could

00:00:20.960 --> 00:00:24.150
be something. I know the Lord's done

00:00:24.160 --> 00:00:26.509
something for you this year so far. We

00:00:26.519 --> 00:00:29.550
still have 30-some days left until the

00:00:29.560 --> 00:00:31.910
first of the year, until January of

00:00:31.920 --> 00:00:36.069
2025, but look at what He's done in

00:00:36.079 --> 00:00:39.190
2024. And what a time in America. You know,

00:00:39.200 --> 00:00:41.430
you can do it wherever you live,

00:00:41.440 --> 00:00:43.990
just giving God praise and thanksgiving

00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:47.670
for everything He's done in your life. He

00:00:47.680 --> 00:00:52.349
has been so merciful in so many areas. I

00:00:52.359 --> 00:00:54.430
look back, I mean, just looking back at

00:00:54.440 --> 00:00:56.510
all of the things He's done this year,

00:00:56.520 --> 00:00:59.270
you know, with Megan and how far she's

00:00:59.280 --> 00:01:01.830
come. We've had a great year with her,

00:01:01.840 --> 00:01:03.549
seeing healings come and

00:01:03.559 --> 00:01:06.230
manifestations of the glory with the

00:01:06.240 --> 00:01:08.990
outpouring at the Tent Revival,

00:01:09.000 --> 00:01:11.870
seeing the Shekinah Glory Cloud, going to

00:01:11.880 --> 00:01:13.710
see Billy Burke and smelling the

00:01:13.720 --> 00:01:15.670
fragrance of the Holy

00:01:15.670 --> 00:01:15.680
Spirit—so

00:01:15.680 --> 00:01:19.230
many amazing things, just

00:01:19.240 --> 00:01:21.590
supernatural. The words that the Lord

00:01:21.600 --> 00:01:24.149
has given me

00:01:24.149 --> 00:01:24.159
protected

00:01:24.159 --> 00:01:26.550
President Trump from the assassination

00:01:26.550 --> 00:01:26.560
attempts

00:01:26.560 --> 00:01:29.270
twice, maybe even three times.

00:01:29.280 --> 00:01:32.749
Seeing a Red Wave like the Lord gave

00:01:32.759 --> 00:01:35.069
us. There are so many things that you can

00:01:35.079 --> 00:01:37.310
be thankful for: that we have a new

00:01:37.320 --> 00:01:40.270
president coming and helping bring a

00:01:40.270 --> 00:01:40.280
turnaround to

00:01:40.280 --> 00:01:43.389
America, and just a

00:01:43.399 --> 00:01:46.190
lot to be thankful for even going into

00:01:46.200 --> 00:01:49.830
2025, regardless of all the

00:01:49.840 --> 00:01:52.069
rumors of wars and all the things

00:01:52.079 --> 00:01:54.190
that you see on the news. Yeah, there's

00:01:54.200 --> 00:01:56.709
drama, but there's always something to be

00:01:56.719 --> 00:01:59.230
thankful for. There's always something to

00:01:59.240 --> 00:02:02.109
give God praise for. You know, a lot of

00:02:02.119 --> 00:02:03.990
what happened with Abraham—one of

00:02:04.000 --> 00:02:06.029
my favorite verses is that Abraham

00:02:06.039 --> 00:02:07.870
staggered not at the promise of God

00:02:07.880 --> 00:02:09.869
through unbelief, but was strong in faith,

00:02:09.879 --> 00:02:12.350
giving glory to God. He gave praise to

00:02:12.360 --> 00:02:15.990
God even before he saw the full

00:02:16.000 --> 00:02:17.830
manifestation of what he was believing

00:02:17.840 --> 00:02:20.869
for. Even in the

00:02:20.879 --> 00:02:23.869
deadness of Sarah's womb, he was

00:02:23.879 --> 00:02:27.309
thankful, giving glory to God. That was

00:02:27.319 --> 00:02:30.110
him giving praise, being thankful.

00:02:30.120 --> 00:02:32.390
I give You praise, Lord; I thank You for

00:02:32.400 --> 00:02:33.830
all that You've done, all that You're

00:02:33.840 --> 00:02:37.030
going to do, and all You continue to do.

00:02:37.040 --> 00:02:39.670
And so, I just take a time, even

00:02:39.680 --> 00:02:43.390
right now, to say, 'God, thank You.'Thank You,

00:02:43.400 --> 00:02:45.670
Father, for all that You provided:

00:02:45.680 --> 00:02:48.949
for our clothes, our house,

00:02:48.959 --> 00:02:51.149
the car we drive,

00:02:51.159 --> 00:02:53.350
the air we breathe,

00:02:53.360 --> 00:02:55.910
the sun that shines, the trees

00:02:55.920 --> 00:02:57.949
that are around the earth. Father,

00:02:57.959 --> 00:03:00.309
for all of the grass and for the

00:03:00.319 --> 00:03:02.550
water and for all the things that He

00:03:02.560 --> 00:03:03.789
provided. He could have been a really

00:03:03.799 --> 00:03:07.990
boring God. He could have had one

00:03:08.000 --> 00:03:10.710
kind of

00:03:10.710 --> 00:03:10.720
tree—it

00:03:10.720 --> 00:03:12.350
could have been an oak tree or

00:03:12.350 --> 00:03:12.360
whatever—and

00:03:12.360 --> 00:03:14.509
that was the only tree He made. He could

00:03:14.519 --> 00:03:17.350
have made one flower, could have made one

00:03:17.360 --> 00:03:19.470
bird,

00:03:21.000 --> 00:03:24.509
but He made all

00:03:24.519 --> 00:03:27.470
kinds of things for us richly to enjoy.

00:03:27.480 --> 00:03:29.830
Isn't that amazing? He made all the

00:03:29.840 --> 00:03:31.309
different things: all the different kinds

00:03:31.319 --> 00:03:34.509
of cows, all the different kinds of dogs.

00:03:34.519 --> 00:03:35.789
You may say, 'Well, I don't like that kind

00:03:35.799 --> 00:03:37.149
of dog,'but He gave you another kind of

00:03:37.159 --> 00:03:39.509
choice. Maybe you like cats;

00:03:39.519 --> 00:03:40.750
He gave you all kinds of different

00:03:41.439 --> 00:03:44.949
cats. He is so

00:03:44.959 --> 00:03:47.149
exceedingly abundantly above all that we

00:03:47.159 --> 00:03:48.910
dare ask or

00:03:48.920 --> 00:03:51.390
think. And there's something—you say, 'I

00:03:51.400 --> 00:03:53.270
don't have anything to be thankful for.'Oh,

00:03:53.270 --> 00:03:53.280
I guarantee

00:03:53.280 --> 00:03:55.429
you, if you just stop and

00:03:55.439 --> 00:03:58.309
think just a little bit, you can think of

00:03:58.319 --> 00:04:00.429
something. I have something to be

00:04:00.439 --> 00:04:03.030
thankful for. And it's just

00:04:03.030 --> 00:04:03.040
like—when

00:04:03.040 --> 00:04:05.670
you give God praise and you

00:04:05.680 --> 00:04:09.110
give God worth and you take the time to

00:04:09.120 --> 00:04:11.830
give Him an offering of thanksgiving in

00:04:11.840 --> 00:04:14.789
every area of your life, it brings the

00:04:14.799 --> 00:04:17.909
glory down, because when praises go up,

00:04:17.919 --> 00:04:20.830
blessings come down.

00:04:20.840 --> 00:04:25.390
He is worthy of it. He

00:04:25.390 --> 00:04:25.400
is the El Elyon,

00:04:25.400 --> 00:04:28.070
the Most High. He's the Jehovah Jireh, He's

00:04:28.080 --> 00:04:30.870
everything that I need. He has it, and

00:04:30.880 --> 00:04:33.909
He's made it

00:04:33.919 --> 00:04:36.270
for us richly to enjoy. I

00:04:36.280 --> 00:04:38.909
love that scripture. And so, you know what?

00:04:38.919 --> 00:04:40.150
You may say,

00:04:40.160 --> 00:04:42.790
'Well, I'm not all the way where I

00:04:42.800 --> 00:04:44.790
need to be in overcoming,'but I saw a little

00:04:44.800 --> 00:04:48.110
bit of change this year. I saw a little

00:04:48.120 --> 00:04:51.029
bit. I may not have my full manifestation

00:04:51.039 --> 00:04:53.670
of what I've been believing for, but I

00:04:53.680 --> 00:04:56.230
saw some

00:04:56.240 --> 00:04:57.790
change.

00:04:57.800 --> 00:05:01.390
Noah released the dove, and it came back

00:05:01.390 --> 00:05:01.400
with

00:05:01.400 --> 00:05:04.390
just a little olive branch. But Noah

00:05:04.400 --> 00:05:07.110
knew that was a sign that

00:05:07.120 --> 00:05:08.629
the flood was

00:05:08.639 --> 00:05:12.590
over, and he gave God praise for it. Just

00:05:12.600 --> 00:05:14.990
that little olive leaf, that

00:05:15.000 --> 00:05:17.550
little twig in its mouth, represented

00:05:17.560 --> 00:05:20.749
that the flood was over and that God

00:05:20.759 --> 00:05:22.749
doesn't dangle a carrot. Like Billy Burke

00:05:22.759 --> 00:05:25.390
said to us, God doesn't dangle a carrot

00:05:25.400 --> 00:05:28.469
and heal partway just to

00:05:28.479 --> 00:05:31.749
lead you on. God's a full manifestation

00:05:31.759 --> 00:05:35.309
God. So if you've seen something, there's

00:05:35.319 --> 00:05:38.390
hope in that. There's hope in

00:05:38.400 --> 00:05:40.790
that little bit of a turnaround. That's

00:05:40.800 --> 00:05:43.710
that olive leaf that you've got today to

00:05:43.720 --> 00:05:46.110
say, 'God, I have something to be thankful

00:05:46.120 --> 00:05:49.390
for today,'regardless

00:05:49.390 --> 00:05:49.400
of how

00:05:49.400 --> 00:05:52.270
much more you have

00:05:52.270 --> 00:05:52.280
to go.

00:05:52.280 --> 00:05:55.870
You got the olive leaf; it was the sign

00:05:55.880 --> 00:05:59.110
that the flood was over. In your life,

00:05:59.120 --> 00:06:02.189
you may have no pain in your elbow, and

00:06:02.199 --> 00:06:03.950
it may just be a little spot in your

00:06:03.960 --> 00:06:06.469
elbow that doesn't have pain. Give

00:06:06.479 --> 00:06:08.430
God praise for that no pain in that

00:06:08.440 --> 00:06:10.589
elbow, or that little toe that doesn't hurt

00:06:10.589 --> 00:06:10.599
anymore.

00:06:10.599 --> 00:06:13.309
You may go, 'Oh,

00:06:13.319 --> 00:06:15.950
but everything else hurts so

00:06:15.950 --> 00:06:15.960
bad,'but

00:06:15.960 --> 00:06:17.870
give God praise for it because that's

00:06:17.880 --> 00:06:20.550
the sign that the flood is turning around

00:06:20.560 --> 00:06:24.510
in your life. Believe that today. Reach

00:06:24.520 --> 00:06:27.150
out today and give God praise for every

00:06:27.160 --> 00:06:29.070
single thing He's done. It may just

00:06:29.080 --> 00:06:32.390
be, 'My toenail doesn't hurt today,

00:06:32.390 --> 00:06:32.400
Lord,'but

00:06:32.400 --> 00:06:35.350
it's a sign that the flood is subsiding

00:06:35.360 --> 00:06:38.270
in your life. That storm that was sent to

00:06:38.280 --> 00:06:40.510
try to kill, steal, and destroy you and

00:06:40.520 --> 00:06:42.510
pull you down all the way

00:06:42.510 --> 00:06:42.520
under—there's

00:06:42.520 --> 00:06:45.550
a sign of relief today.

00:06:45.560 --> 00:06:47.110
That's what you have to grab

00:06:47.110 --> 00:06:47.120
onto:

00:06:47.120 --> 00:06:49.950
those glimmers of

00:06:49.960 --> 00:06:52.749
hope. My hope is built on nothing less

00:06:52.759 --> 00:06:55.710
than Jesus'blood and His righteousness.

00:06:55.720 --> 00:06:59.629
I believe with all my heart that today

00:06:59.639 --> 00:07:04.150
our olive leaf is here, and we

00:07:04.160 --> 00:07:06.189
give God praise for that olive leaf. I

00:07:06.199 --> 00:07:08.869
tell Diana all the time we see the

00:07:08.879 --> 00:07:11.309
change and the tide is changing with

00:07:11.319 --> 00:07:14.589
Megan on a day-to-day basis. Regardless

00:07:14.589 --> 00:07:14.599
of

00:07:14.599 --> 00:07:16.749
if she may have a bad day the next day,

00:07:16.759 --> 00:07:19.070
we say, 'Nope, we're still standing on the

00:07:19.080 --> 00:07:22.550
good

00:07:22.550 --> 00:07:22.560
day.'We

00:07:22.560 --> 00:07:24.830
had several good days this year.

00:07:24.840 --> 00:07:27.390
We had some bad days, but we're not

00:07:27.390 --> 00:07:27.400
focused

00:07:27.400 --> 00:07:29.150
on the bad days; we're focused on the

00:07:29.160 --> 00:07:30.070
good days.

00:07:30.070 --> 00:07:30.080
Because

00:07:30.080 --> 00:07:31.790
you've got to give God praise for

00:07:31.800 --> 00:07:33.990
every single good day and say, 'You know

00:07:34.000 --> 00:07:36.270
what? We may have had a bad day today, but

00:07:36.280 --> 00:07:38.189
we're going to have a good day

00:07:38.189 --> 00:07:38.199
tomorrow.'Regardless

00:07:38.199 --> 00:07:40.230
of your

00:07:40.240 --> 00:07:42.390
circumstances,

00:07:42.400 --> 00:07:44.629
joy comes in the morning. That's exactly

00:07:44.639 --> 00:07:47.589
right. I

00:07:47.599 --> 00:07:50.149
believe that we can call those things

00:07:50.159 --> 00:07:52.110
that be not as though they were by

00:07:52.120 --> 00:07:55.990
speaking to our circumstances to change.

00:07:56.000 --> 00:07:58.390
You may be all alone in this holiday

00:07:58.400 --> 00:08:00.430
season. You may be sitting there on

00:08:00.440 --> 00:08:03.070
your couch and you're all by yourself

00:08:03.080 --> 00:08:05.070
and you're thinking, 'Man, nobody cares

00:08:05.080 --> 00:08:08.550
about me.'But Diana and I are here

00:08:08.560 --> 00:08:10.430
and we're here for

00:08:10.440 --> 00:08:12.550
you. We're praying for you. Know that

00:08:12.560 --> 00:08:15.990
we're lifting you up before the Father.

00:08:16.000 --> 00:08:19.189
That hit me—somebody's really

00:08:19.199 --> 00:08:21.790
struggling. I felt that

00:08:21.800 --> 00:08:25.270
intercession hit me. Somebody's out

00:08:25.280 --> 00:08:27.550
there believing for someone to be their

00:08:27.560 --> 00:08:30.110
friend, and I just want to let you all

00:08:30.120 --> 00:08:32.110
know we're your friend.

00:08:32.120 --> 00:08:33.709
We're in your corner; we're believing

00:08:33.719 --> 00:08:37.029
with you. We stand with you when you feel,

00:08:37.039 --> 00:08:38.870
'I don't have anybody out there that

00:08:38.880 --> 00:08:42.829
loves me. Why am I even on this earth? God

00:08:42.839 --> 00:08:45.870
doesn't care about me; He's forgotten

00:08:45.880 --> 00:08:49.389
about me. I'm broken. I have no friends,

00:08:49.399 --> 00:08:52.070
no wife, no husband. All my

00:08:52.080 --> 00:08:55.710
relatives have passed on. I have no kids.

00:08:55.720 --> 00:08:58.829
I'm all alone on this holiday season. Why

00:08:58.839 --> 00:09:01.790
am I still here?'But God has a plan for

00:09:01.800 --> 00:09:03.670
you, and this will be the best year

00:09:03.680 --> 00:09:06.030
you've ever lived so far.

00:09:06.030 --> 00:09:06.040
In

00:09:06.040 --> 00:09:09.269
2024, we're going to find some friends.

00:09:09.279 --> 00:09:11.829
Say that: 'I'm going to make myself

00:09:11.839 --> 00:09:13.470
friendly, and I'm going to find some

00:09:13.470 --> 00:09:13.480
friends.'The

00:09:13.480 --> 00:09:15.949
year is not over; you

00:09:15.959 --> 00:09:19.030
don't have to be down and out

00:09:19.030 --> 00:09:19.040
or

00:09:19.040 --> 00:09:22.310
sad. It's a time to have joy in

00:09:22.320 --> 00:09:24.590
your heart, a smile on your face, and a

00:09:24.600 --> 00:09:27.269
song in your heart, because Jesus loves

00:09:27.279 --> 00:09:30.069
you. Just like we say every day:

00:09:30.079 --> 00:09:31.990
put a smile on your face and a song in

00:09:32.000 --> 00:09:34.550
your heart; Jesus loves you. You know, that

00:09:34.560 --> 00:09:37.110
came from my dad. My mom had a lot of

00:09:37.120 --> 00:09:39.389
hard times whenever they were going

00:09:39.399 --> 00:09:43.389
through a lot of poverty, and my mom

00:09:43.399 --> 00:09:45.949
would fuss around the house a lot.

00:09:45.959 --> 00:09:47.870
My dad would always tell my mom, 'You

00:09:47.880 --> 00:09:49.670
need to put a smile on your face and a

00:09:49.680 --> 00:09:52.550
song in your heart,'because she would be

00:09:52.560 --> 00:09:54.710
so fussy about it.

00:09:54.720 --> 00:09:56.949
That came right up out of him.

00:09:56.959 --> 00:10:00.190
As a kid, that's

00:10:00.200 --> 00:10:02.230
always been in my heart;

00:10:02.230 --> 00:10:02.240
it's

00:10:02.240 --> 00:10:04.030
always stirred me.

00:10:04.040 --> 00:10:05.870
But that came

00:10:05.880 --> 00:10:08.710
out of my dad because we had such a hard

00:10:08.720 --> 00:10:10.910
time growing

00:10:10.920 --> 00:10:15.030
up. They struggled a lot, but we

00:10:15.040 --> 00:10:15.949
made it

00:10:15.959 --> 00:10:18.949
through. I met

00:10:18.959 --> 00:10:21.069
Diana, and it's been the greatest thing

00:10:21.079 --> 00:10:23.710
of my life, just going through

00:10:23.720 --> 00:10:25.870
life with her. And yet we've had our

00:10:25.880 --> 00:10:28.030
challenges, and yet it seemed like I left

00:10:28.040 --> 00:10:30.430
Mom and Dad's mess and we had our

00:10:30.430 --> 00:10:30.440
own

00:10:30.440 --> 00:10:32.509
mess started up. But God has been

00:10:32.519 --> 00:10:34.430
faithful, hasn't He, babe? Yes. And He's

00:10:34.440 --> 00:10:36.790
brought us through some trying

00:10:36.800 --> 00:10:39.389
times. But it wasn't

00:10:39.399 --> 00:10:42.069
something that we got overnight. We

00:10:42.079 --> 00:10:45.069
had to believe and keep on keeping on,

00:10:45.079 --> 00:10:48.150
regardless of what we saw in the

00:10:48.160 --> 00:10:50.190
natural. It felt

00:10:50.190 --> 00:10:50.200
like

00:10:50.200 --> 00:10:51.949
we were never going to get out

00:10:51.959 --> 00:10:52.670
of it—poverty

00:10:52.670 --> 00:10:52.680
and

00:10:52.680 --> 00:10:56.470
lack. But with the creative ideas

00:10:56.480 --> 00:11:01.550
to do eBay and Poshmark and Facebook

00:11:01.560 --> 00:11:04.310
Marketplace, thinking, 'How are we going to

00:11:04.320 --> 00:11:06.870
get out of

00:11:06.870 --> 00:11:06.880
this?'when

00:11:06.880 --> 00:11:08.150
you're going from

00:11:08.160 --> 00:11:10.269
paycheck to paycheck and you

00:11:10.279 --> 00:11:13.150
think, 'I don't have any

00:11:13.150 --> 00:11:13.160
ideas.'But

00:11:13.160 --> 00:11:17.910
God, who is rich in mercy, will

00:11:17.920 --> 00:11:20.710
give you a creative idea to do something

00:11:20.720 --> 00:11:22.310
different and then give you favor with

00:11:22.320 --> 00:11:26.389
thrift store owners. Who knew? You

00:11:26.399 --> 00:11:28.110
walk in there and start talking to

00:11:28.120 --> 00:11:30.590
somebody, and you let that favor of

00:11:30.600 --> 00:11:33.230
God shine on you. You

00:11:33.240 --> 00:11:34.870
don't go in there and start

00:11:34.880 --> 00:11:36.509
witnessing and hitting them in

00:11:36.519 --> 00:11:38.190
the head with the Bible. You let your

00:11:38.200 --> 00:11:40.030
light shine through your eyes. You

00:11:40.040 --> 00:11:42.590
just go in there—man, God's good. You

00:11:42.600 --> 00:11:43.870
just have that

00:11:43.880 --> 00:11:47.310
attitude of, 'I know who I am in Christ,

00:11:47.320 --> 00:11:49.990
and I'm going to display Jesus

00:11:49.990 --> 00:11:50.000
